OL,3,CPassover UK: An ancient Jewish
OL,4,Cfestival in modern Britain
OL,6,FThe very abridged story goes that in
OL,7,Froughly 1400 B.C., the Israelites were
OL,8,Fheld in captivity by the Pharaoh.
OL,10,FAfter God sends 10 plagues to the
OL,11,FEgyptians, the Israelites escape when
OL,12,Fthe Red Sea splits, offering them a
OL,13,Fsafe passage into the desert.
OL,15,FThose Israelites became the Jewish
OL,16,Fpeople.
OL,18,FPassover is so old that even Jesus
OL,19,Fobserved it - the 'Last Supper' is
OL,20,Ftraditionally believed to have been a
OL,21,FPassover 'Seder' meal.
