OL,3,CPassover UK: An ancient Jewish
OL,4,Cfestival in modern Britain
OL,6,FThe 'Seder' features lots of symbolic
OL,7,Ffoods meant to evoke the experience of
OL,8,Fthe Israelites: salt water represents
OL,9,Fthe tears shed by the slaves, while
OL,10,Fbitter herbs and horseradish are a
OL,11,Freminder of the bitterness of
OL,12,Fcaptivity.
OL,14,FThere is even a dish called 'Charoset'
OL,15,Fwhich is supposed to look like the
OL,16,Fcement used to build Pharoah's cities.
OL,17,FThe ingredients list depends on family
OL,18,Fheritage.
