OL,3,CPassover UK: An ancient Jewish
OL,4,Cfestival in modern Britain
OL,6,FPassover may be a Jewish festival, but
OL,7,Fthe story has long attracted people of
OL,8,Fall faiths and none. Moses is
OL,9,Fmentioned frequently in both the New
OL,10,FTestament and the Qur'an, while
OL,11,FAmerican slaves used to sing about the
OL,12,FExodus in songs yearning for their own
OL,13,Ffreedom.
OL,15,FIn this modern age, religion is often
OL,16,Fseen as restrictive, old-fashioned,
OL,17,Fand more about what you cannot do than
OL,18,Fcan, but what really came across
OL,19,Fduring the weeks we spent filming was
OL,20,Fthe sense of joy that Passover
OL,21,Finspires.
OL,1,Wz5~k4~k7}hw1 ~k4~sj5j5~s1 G     G9/11
